00:34:11,159 --> 00:34:14,942
integrating merchandise even more tightly, using it as rewards for playing the game and

631
00:34:14,962 --> 00:34:19,086
maybe sort of signing certain milestones in the game to the act of getting discounts or

632
00:34:19,126 --> 00:34:19,807
free merchandise?

633
00:34:20,287 --> 00:34:23,468
I think for us, it's definitely something that's been on our minds,

634
00:34:23,488 --> 00:34:25,869
and it's something I've seen other games do to interesting effect,

635
00:34:26,189 --> 00:34:28,750
but I think what's very important for us is that the games we craft

636
00:34:28,990 --> 00:34:32,191
are meant to feel like small worlds you visit for a small amount of time,

637
00:34:32,231 --> 00:34:34,152
and we want those to feel deeply authentic.

638
00:34:34,532 --> 00:34:36,853
And so our gift shop, while not perhaps authentic,

639
00:34:37,153 --> 00:34:37,893
is meant to feel...

640
00:34:38,534 --> 00:34:42,536
as close as possible to the idea that you're visiting maybe a small place in Altos village

641
00:34:42,796 --> 00:34:46,058
and purchasing something as you've spent some time there. And I think for us we don't want

642
00:34:46,078 --> 00:34:49,861
to integrate merchandise in a way that will detract from the quality of the act of playing

643
00:34:49,901 --> 00:34:52,482
the game. But I think for the right game it's absolutely an option.

644
00:34:55,488 --> 00:35:03,916
Thanks for the talk. Very fascinating. I was curious, you mentioned this pretty dramatic spread between revenue from iOS versus Android.

645
00:35:03,936 --> 00:35:04,176
Sure.

646
00:35:04,617 --> 00:35:10,702
And I was wondering, have you noticed any differences in the products that players are interested in?

647
00:35:10,842 --> 00:35:11,843
You know, is it sort of...

648
00:35:12,244 --> 00:35:16,145
You know, this kind of thing is for some reason more popular among iOS players, whereas Android

649
00:35:16,205 --> 00:35:17,166
gravitates toward this.

650
00:35:17,686 --> 00:35:18,166
Great question.

