00:35:28,050 --> 00:35:29,111
players in our store?

654
00:35:29,711 --> 00:35:33,252
And for us, while we're not seeing that, what we are seeing that I want to draw attention to

655
00:35:33,632 --> 00:35:36,713
are the regions to which those merchandise items are being purchased.

656
00:35:37,153 --> 00:35:40,294
A disproportionate amount of our overseas shipping goes to Android players

657
00:35:40,835 --> 00:35:44,476
among the shipping that goes for the in-game items, the items purchased in-game.

658
00:35:44,776 --> 00:35:47,517
So a lot of the items purchased in-game through our Android integration

659
00:35:47,877 --> 00:35:50,978
are done to Russia, China, Japan, Vietnam,

660
00:35:51,418 --> 00:35:56,240
whereas the disproportionate amount of the iOS purchases go to Canada, the UK, and the United States.

661
00:35:56,925 --> 00:36:00,227
And do you have sort of unsupported countries?

662
00:36:00,287 --> 00:36:05,029
Has it become a problem at all where somebody will order something from, you know, the far corners of the earth

663
00:36:05,089 --> 00:36:08,050
and you have to call them and be like, we actually don't ship there or whatever?

664
00:36:08,090 --> 00:36:10,812
That's a great question. So are there any unsupported countries for us?

665
00:36:10,852 --> 00:36:13,913
Have we run into problems where players want to buy a thing, but we can't send a thing?

666
00:36:15,134 --> 00:36:18,976
There haven't, and part of that is that for this particular solution we chose Shopify,

667
00:36:19,216 --> 00:36:22,999
they enable the sort of e-commerce seller to sell worldwide,

668
00:36:23,379 --> 00:36:25,901
and we've, our shipping solution in the form of Amplify,

669
00:36:25,921 --> 00:36:28,283
or the warehouse solution we chose, also supports that,

670
00:36:28,543 --> 00:36:31,305
but it's absolutely a thing that as a merchandise creator you have to consider.

671
00:36:31,605 --> 00:36:35,628
Because, for example, if you've chosen as somebody to not pay a warehousing solution,

672
00:36:35,648 --> 00:36:37,649
and stock your merch in your house or in your office,

673
00:36:37,869 --> 00:36:41,071
you're only going to be able to ship where you've set up the capacity to do so,

674
00:36:41,091 --> 00:36:42,252
and have the bandwidth to do so.

675
00:36:42,572 --> 00:36:46,058
So we haven't run into it, but it's absolutely a thing you have to preemptively avoid

676
00:36:46,338 --> 00:36:48,782
by choosing scaffolding that allows you to ship worldwide.

677
00:36:49,182 --> 00:36:49,863
Awesome. Thanks.

